Spouse: Thornton MYERS. Christina GANS and Thornton MYERS were married. Children were: Jacob Lashley "Uncle Jake" MYERS.

Frances "Fanny" GANT was born on 26 May 1842 in Kentucky. She died on 18 November 1917 at the age of 75 in Cameron, Clinton, Missouri. She was buried on 20 November 1917. Burial was in Stony Point Cemetery. Parents: William GANT and Lutecia PULLLIAM.Frances Ann "Fannie" GANT was born (date unknown).

Spouse: David Presley WOODRUFF. Frances Ann "Fannie" GANT and David Presley WOODRUFF were married on 6 February 1873 in Johnson Co., Missouri. Children were: Bettie Jane WOODRUFF.

Henry O. GANT was born (date unknown).

Spouse: Katherine BOWERSOX. Katherine BOWERSOX and Henry O. GANT were married in 1886.

Mae Y. GANT was born on 11 April 1872 in Ray Co., Missouri. She died on 10 February 1955 at the age of 82 in Polo, Caldwell, Missouri. She was buried on 13 February 1955 in Zimmerman Cemetery, Caldwell, Missouri. Parents: Duncan GANT and Louisa GRIMES.

Spouse: William S. BATHGATE. Mae Y. GANT and William S. BATHGATE were married on 4 June 1893 in Caldwell Co., Missouri. The bride was of Knoxville, Ray Co., the groom of Polo, Caldwell Co. Children were: Thomas Gant BATHGATE, Eula May BATHGATE.

Marvin GANT was born about 1903 in Missouri. Parents: Samuel "Sam" GANT and Celia MUSSELMAN.Opal C. GANT was born on 23 March 1899 in Jamesport Twp., Daviess, Missouri. She died on 11 November 1953 at the age of 54 in Kansas City, Jackson, Missouri. She was buried in Jamesport Masonic Cemetery, Daviess, Missouri. Parents: Samuel "Sam" GANT and Celia MUSSELMAN.

Spouse: Leslie O. LANGFORD. Opal C. GANT and Leslie O. LANGFORD were married about 1919. Children were: Mary K. LANGFORD, Ralph E. LANGFORD, Nila M. LANGFORD, Hazel I. LANGFORD.

Samuel "Sam" GANT was born on 15 June 1868 in Ray Co., Missouri. He died on 22 April 1948 at the age of 79. He was buried in Jamesport Masonic Cemetery, Daviess, Missouri. Samuel was a livestock buyer at Jamesport in 1920.

Spouse: Celia MUSSELMAN. Celia MUSSELMAN and Samuel "Sam" GANT were married on 28 February 1894 in Daviess Co., Missouri. Bride and groom were of Gallatin. They married at the residence of Amos Musselman. Children were: Opal C. GANT, Marvin GANT.

William GANT was born (date unknown).

Spouse: Lutecia PULLLIAM. Lutecia PULLLIAM and William GANT were married. Children were: Frances "Fanny" GANT.

Leopholdine "Tena" GANTER was born in 1843 in Baden, Saxony, Germany. She died on 27 January 1921 at the age of 78 in Livingston Co., Missouri. She was buried in Plainview Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri.

Spouse: George A. GARDNER. Leopholdine "Tena" GANTER and George A. GARDNER were married about 1867. Children were: Frances Amelia GARDNER, Louisa Henrietta "Lula" GARDNER, Elizabeth R. "Lizzie" GARDNER.

Andrew GANTNER was born (date unknown).

Spouse: Rose DIRINGER. Rose DIRINGER and Andrew GANTNER were married. Children were: Joseph F. GANTNER.

Joseph F. GANTNER was born on 7 March 1864 in Booneville, Boone, Missouri. He died on 21 April 1950 at the age of 86 in Jennings, St. Louis, Missouri. He was buried on 24 April 1950 in Pilot Grove, Cooper, Missouri. Burial was in St. Josephs Cemetery. Parents: Andrew GANTNER and Rose DIRINGER.

Spouse: Lena HOFFMAN. Lena HOFFMAN and Joseph F. GANTNER were married on 2 May 1888 in Cooper Co., Missouri. Bride and groom were of Cooper Co., Missouri. Children were: Sylvester John GANTNER.

Marilyn GANTNER was born on 24 January 1919 in Missouri. Parents: Sylvester John GANTNER and Faye Cleone LIVICK.

Spouse: Dr. Joseph F. GALE. Marilyn GANTNER and Dr. Joseph F. GALE were married on 26 December 1942 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. Bride and groom were of Chillicothe. Children were: Pamela Karen "Pam" GALE, Barbara Sue GALE, Patricia Jo "Pat" GALE.

Sylvester John GANTNER was born on 31 December 1891 in Pilot Grove, Daviess, Missouri. He died on 25 July 1952 at the age of 60 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. He was buried on 29 July 1952 in Edgewood Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. Parents: Joseph F. GANTNER and Lena HOFFMAN.

Spouse: Faye Cleone LIVICK. Faye Cleone LIVICK and Sylvester John GANTNER were married on 28 April 1917 in Kansas City, Jackson, Missouri. Bride and groom were of Chillicothe. Children were: Marilyn GANTNER.

Spouse: RHODES. Carolyn GARBER and RHODES were married.

Chester Scott GARBER was born on 16 September 1922 in Carroll Co., Missouri. He died on 4 November 2014 at the age of 92 in Independence, Jackson, Missouri. His home was in Tina. He was buried on 9 November 2014 in Coloma Cemetery, Carroll, Missouri. He attended Stokes Mound grade school and graduated from Tina High School. Parents: James Austin GARBER and Julie Faye HANSEN.

Spouse: Lucille SUMMERS. Lucille SUMMERS and Chester Scott GARBER were married on 31 December 1947 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri.

Spouse: Laura Mae WHITE. Laura Mae WHITE and Chester Scott GARBER were married on 16 June 1983.

Clyde I. GARBER was born on 6 November 1919 in Hale, Carroll, Missouri. He died about 1986 at the age of 67 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. He was buried in Hale Cemetery, Carroll, Missouri. He served in the Army in World War II. Parents: Hugh Salamon GARBER and Jessie Ruth DAUGHERTY.

Spouse: Phyllis FIFER. Phyllis FIFER and Clyde I. GARBER were married on 12 September 1948 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. Children were: Diana GARBER, Debra GARBER, Bruce GARBER, Steven GARBER.

David GARBER was born (date unknown). Parents: Harold "Bud" GARBER and Jessie June FORSYTHE.

Spouse: Charla . Charla and David GARBER were married.

Spouse: James BECKER. Debra GARBER and James BECKER were married.

He was buried on 2 February 1961 in Coloma Cemetery, Carroll, Missouri. He served in World War II. Parents: Hugh Salamon GARBER and Jessie Ruth DAUGHERTY.

Spouse: Mildred Verlee CORF. Mildred Verlee CORF and Earl Edward GARBER were married.

Flossie Irene GARBER was born on 13 March 1912 in Carroll Co., Missouri. She died on 25 December 1977 at the age of 65 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. She was buried in Avalon Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. Parents: Peter Aaron GARBER and Dora Ruth FIELDS.

Spouse: Ivan Lavon EVANS. Flossie Irene GARBER and Ivan Lavon EVANS were married on 16 April 1938 in Olathe, Johnson, Kansas.

Frances GARBER was born (date unknown). Parents: Hugh Salamon GARBER and Jessie Ruth DAUGHERTY.

Spouse: Larry SAALE. Frances GARBER and Larry SAALE were married.

Harold "Bud" GARBER was born on 4 December 1931 in Hale, Carroll, Missouri. He died on 24 November 2016 at the age of 84 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. He died in a Chillicothe rest home; his residence had been in Hale. He was buried on 27 November 2016 in Avalon Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. He graduated from Tina High School in 1949. He served in the Air Force in the Korean War. Parents: Hezekiah GARBER and Alta DAUGHERTY.

Spouse: Jessie June FORSYTHE. Jessie June FORSYTHE and Harold "Bud" GARBER were married on 15 June 1951 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. Children were: David GARBER, Ron GARBER, Beverly GARBER.
